{Attachments cont'd.}
We saw a large seed drill which needed a powerful tractor to pull it. In the buildings there was also a plough and disc harrow. Outside were several other kinds of harrow for breaking up the soil.
{The Combine Harvester. { This vehicle cuts wheat. Inside it's like a stomach: it cuts the stems, chews the corn, which then goes up an elevator and shoots out into a trailer which is pulled by a tractor alongside. Its cab is quite big. It is not built fore speed. It makes 940 cuts per minute at 31 to 67 rpm. The cutter has a double sickle that gives a clean cut. The straw drops out at the back.
